      • isPropertyAccessor

        public static com.google.common.base.Predicate<Element> isPropertyAccessor()
        Returns a predicate that accepts property accessors. A property accessor is a no-argument method (typically a "getter") which returns a piece of state for an object.

      • isPropertyMutator

        public static com.google.common.base.Predicate<Element> isPropertyMutator()
        Returns a predicate that accepts property mutators. A property mutator is single argument method (typically a "setter") which modifies a piece of state for an object.

      • isProperty

      • toPropertyName

        public static com.google.common.base.Function<Element,String> toPropertyName()
        Returns a function that transforms a property element into a property name. A property name is the identifier (typically a method name without the "get" or "set" prefix) of a piece of state for an object.

        The transformation will fail with an IllegalStateException if the element being mapped is not a property element.

      • toPropertyType

        public static com.google.common.base.Function<Element,TypeMirror> toPropertyType()
        Returns a function that transforms a property element into a property type. A property type is the type returned by an accessor or accepted as the single parameter to a mutator.

        The transformation will fail with an IllegalStateException if the element being mapped is not a property element.
